Trucking Profitability Dashboard

This project helps a small trucking operation decide which loads to take by calculating true profit per mile using both fixed and fuel costs.

Pipeline

1. Raw load & fuel data (CSV input)
2. Data cleaning & validation (handles invalid and messy inputs)
3. Metrics calculation:
-Rate per mile
-Profit per mile
-Fuel cost per mile
4. Database Storage (SQLite)
5. Query analysis:
-Profit by load type
-Daily performance 
-Load-level profitability classification
Key Features
- Handles messy real-world data (invalid values, formatting issues)
- Calculates true profitability using both fixed and fuel-based costs
- Stores structured data in SQLite for fast querying
- Provides actionable insights for load selection decisions
- Separates data pipeline, metrics, and query logic for scalability

Example Output(Used to evaluate load profitability and daily performance)
Type         Average Profit/Mi     Total Profit        Load count
______________________________________________________________________
scrap      |  13.01          |      765.42 |            7
rebar      |  2.86           |      326.74 |            3
______________________________________________________________________
Date         Miles/Day             Total profit/day    Avg Profit/mile/day
______________________________________________________________________
2026-04-10  | 32       |           453.12 |            14.16
2026-03-10  | 144      |           639.04 |             4.44

Analysis:
-Scrap loads should be prioritized over rebar due to significantly higher profit per mile
-Enables operators to reject low-profit loads that appear profitable on the surface

Future Improvements

- Build a frontend dashboard so non-technical operators can use the system without touching code
- Automate CSV uploads and processing
- Add historical trend tracking
- Improve cost modeling with dynamic fuel and maintenance inputs

Note: Real business data in not included in this repo sample datasets are provided for demonstration purposes.